<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870401-0056 </DOCNO><HL> Reynolds andamp; Reynolds SuedBy a Tennessee Company</HL><DD> 04/01/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> REYNA </IN><DATELINE> NASHVILLE, Tenn.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Advanced Voice Technologies Inc., a telecommunications concern, sued Reynolds andamp; Reynolds Co. alleging that the computer services concern pirated one of its computer-voice systems.    In Dayton, Ohio, a Reynolds spokesman denied that the company had misappropriated anything. &quot;We feel there's absolutely no merit to their allegations,&quot; he said. &quot;We're going to fight it.&quot;    The suit, filed in a Detroit federal court, alleges that Reynolds andamp; Reynolds developed a system &quot;substantially identical&quot; to one of Advanced Voice's after the Nashville concern allowed Reynolds to study the system under a confidentiality agreement. It said Reynolds used the technology in a computer system product aimed at automobile dealers. </TEXT></DOC>